meanings.definition: To drag or pull with greater force or speed than someone or something else.
meanings.sent1: The determined squirrel outdragged the other animals to reach the acorn first.
meanings.sent2: The athlete outdragged his competitors to win the race.
meanings.sent3: The snail outdragged the rabbit in a race - who would have thought?
meanings.sent4: Her enthusiasm outdragged any doubts that tried to hold her back.
meanings.sent5: The roaring river outdragged the small stream, carrying debris downstream.
